modules.description: Provides functions for loading and converting image data from files into SDL surfaces, supporting common formats like PNG and JPEG. Works with raw byte arrays and SDL-specific surface structures. Used to integrate bitmap images into 2D game visuals and user interfaces.

This module offers functions for initializing and shutting down image processing, querying version information, and detecting/loading various image formats such as PNG, BMP, JPEG, and GIF from read-write streams. It works with SDL's `Sdlrwops.t` for input/output operations and produces `Sdlsurface.t` objects representing loaded images. Use cases include dynamically loading graphics in applications that require support for multiple image formats or processing images from custom data sources.
